  </music>
</mei>
<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Opening bars 1-4 and repeat bars 5-8: Modal minor feel (Am tonal center). Root-pos voicings
  throughout, emphasizing the vi-iii-IV-vii° progression. Bø7 rendered as full ⑦ø7 (4-note).
- Second section bars 9-12: I (C major) as tonal center asserts itself. Lighter textures, 2nd
  inversion I opens bar 9. V→I cadences in bars 11-12 are diatonic and clear.
- Climax bars 13-16: Return to Am world but with fuller 7th chords (⑥m7 in bars 15, 17) and
  richer LH spacing. Bar 16 has a suspension figure (C5 in melody delays resolution to B4).
- Final cadence bar 17: Am root-position with added 7th (C) in LH, whole-note convergence.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 1-4: LH bass line descends chromatically-adjacent: A2→E2→F2→B2 (root motion by 4ths/5ths).
- Bar 7/15: Dm common tone D in LH held across vi→ii→vi movement.
- Bar 16 suspension: RH G4 anticipates iii before bar resolves; C5 in melody sits over it creating 7th.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Sparse minor opening → two-phrase repeat with register variety (bar 5 RH moves higher) →
  intermediate C-major section (bars 9-12, open spacing, lighter) →
  return to minor with increasing fullness (bars 13-16) → whole-note final Am (bar 17).
-->
